    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0000708 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0000708">
        <rdfs:label>Atypical behavior</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0011446"/>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Psychiatric disturbances</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Behavioral disorders</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Behavioural abnormality</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Behavioral problems</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>SNOMEDCT_US:25786006</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>UMLS:C0233514</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Behavioural/Psychiatric abnormality</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Behavioral abnormality</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:id>HP:0000708</oboInOwl:id>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Behavioural disturbances</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasAlternativeId>HP:0002368</oboInOwl:hasAlternativeId>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Behavioral symptoms</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>UMLS:C0004941</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Behavioural problems</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Behavioural disorders</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Psychiatric disorders</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Behavioral changes</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Behavioral disturbances</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Behavioural symptoms</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>SNOMEDCT_US:277843001</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasAlternativeId>HP:0000715</oboInOwl:hasAlternativeId>
        <rdfs:comment>Atypical behaviors should include or directly affect observable actions. While behavioral disorders often encompass abnormal thoughts, feelings, perceptions, or other cognitions, these alone would not be considered atypical behavioral features.</rdfs:comment>
        <oboInOwl:hasAlternativeId>HP:0002456</oboInOwl:hasAlternativeId>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>Atypical behavior is an abnormality in a person&#39;s actions, which can be controlled or modulated by the will of the individual. While abnormal behaviors can be difficult to control, they are distinct from other abnormal actions that cannot be affected by the individual&#39;s will.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Behavioural changes</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Behavioral/psychiatric abnormalities</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Behavioural/psychiatric abnormality</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:IAO_0000412 rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/hp.owl"/>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8430-6039"/>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199"/>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4142-7153"/>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4422-1708"/>
        <terms:contributor rdf:resource="https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3777-1389"/>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0000709 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0000709">
        <rdfs:label>Psychosis</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_5200430"/>
        <oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Psychosis</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A condition characterized by changes in personality and thought patterns, often accompanied by hallucinations and delusional beliefs, is known as psychosis.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>SNOMEDCT_US:69322001</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:hasDbXref>UMLS:C0033975</oboInOwl:hasDbXref>
        <oboInOwl:id>HP:0000709</oboInOwl:id>
